Text:
Reason for visit (RFV): routine sight test (ST), spectacles scratched. Distance vision (DV) and near vision (NV) with (c) specs very good, wears varifocals (varis).

Symptoms (SX): no headaches (HA), no eyestrain, no pain, no burning, no itching, no redness. Patient (px) has dry eyes. No diplopia. Longstanding occasional floaters since last year in both eyes no changes.

Last eye examination (LEE): 1 year ago.

Previous optical correction (glasses): varifocals approximately 2 years old, now scratched. Wears glasses full time.

General health (GH): okay. No diabetes, no high blood pressure (HBP). Bloods checked twice a year. Cholesterol was raised but normal with statins.

Medication (MEDS): Statins for cholesterol. Hypromellose for dry eye.

Ocular history (OH): no injury. No infection. No surgery, no trauma, no treatment, no hospital (HES) visits. No patching, has been told they have very early signs of dry AMD, uses lubricating eye drops.

Family ocular history (FOH): no glaucoma, no AMD, mum had cataract surgery.

Family medical history (FMH): no high blood pressure (HBP)/diabetes.

Allergies: none.

Smoking: no.

Occupation retired.

Screen use (VDU) use very rare, a few minutes per week, no mobile phone.

Drives yes (with (c) specs).

Hobbies: Spending time with grandchildren, photography, volunteering as a driver.

Contact lens (Cl) wearer no.
